@startuml
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam backgroundColor #fcfcfd
skinparam defaultFontName Helvetica
skinparam defaultFontSize 14
skinparam arrowColor #0f172a
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #fff7d6
skinparam noteBorderColor #b45309
skinparam noteFontColor #334155
skinparam roundcorner 16
title Activity - adm/KnowledgeBase
skinparam activity {
  backgroundColor #f8fafc
  borderColor #0f172a
  fontColor #0f172a
  diamondBackgroundColor #e2e8f0
  diamondBorderColor #1d4ed8
  diamondFontColor #0f172a
  startColor #1d4ed8
  endColor #0f172a
  barColor #1d4ed8
}
start
partition "Observe and Bind" {
:Start from shared flow\nshared/diagrams/shared-reconcile-activity.svg;
:Read desired KnowledgeBase spec, tracked\nstatus, and delete intent;
if ("Tracked or explicit OCI identity present?") then (yes)
:Get the current OCI resource via\nGetKnowledgeBase;
else (no)
:Resolve an existing OCI resource through\nListKnowledgeBases using filters\ncompartmentId, displayName, id;
:Create the OCI resource via\nCreateKnowledgeBase when no reusable match is\nfound;
:Persist the resolved or created OCI identity\ninto status;
endif
}
if ("Delete requested?") then (yes)
partition "Delete" {
:Delete path uses DeleteKnowledgeBase with\nrequired via GetKnowledgeBase or\nListKnowledgeBases to DELETED confirmation;
:Confirm deletion via GetKnowledgeBase or\nListKnowledgeBases until OCI reaches DELETED;
if ("Delete cleanup and finalizer release succeed?") then (yes)
:Remove the finalizer after delete completion;
else (no)
:Stay blocked until cleanup or finalizer\nrelease succeeds;
endif
}
stop
else (no)
partition "Lifecycle Classification" {
if ("OCI state in retryable set?") then (yes)
:Request requeue while OCI remains in CREATING,\nUPDATING, DELETING;
stop
endif
if ("OCI state is outside success targets?") then (yes)
:Return an unsuccessful reconcile result until\nOCI reaches ACTIVE;
stop
endif
}
partition "Ready and Drift Handling" {
:Compare live OCI state against the\nrepo-authored mutation surface;
if ("Force-new or conflicting drift detected?") then (yes)
:Reject drift before OCI mutation for force-new\nfields compartmentId;
stop
endif
if ("Supported mutable drift detected?") then (yes)
:Apply ChangeKnowledgeBaseCompartment,\nUpdateKnowledgeBase only for mutable fields\ndefinedTags, displayName, freeformTags;
else (no)
:Skip the no-op mutation path;
endif
:Run provider helper hooks\ncreate=tfresource.CreateResource,\ntfresource.WaitForWorkRequestWithErrorHandling\nentity=knowledgebase action=CREATED;\nupdate=tfresource.UpdateResource,\ntfresource.WaitForWorkRequestWithErrorHandling\nentity=knowledgebase action=UPDATED;\ndelete=tfresource.DeleteResource,\ntfresource.WaitForWorkRequestWithErrorHandling\nentity=knowledgebase action=DELETED when the\nmatching field-driven path executes;
:Apply explicit follow-up semantics\ncreate=GetWorkRequest -> GetKnowledgeBase;\nupdate=GetWorkRequest -> GetKnowledgeBase;\ndelete=GetWorkRequest ->\nGetKnowledgeBase/ListKnowledgeBases\nconfirm-delete;
:Return success for the ACTIVE success state;
:Project required status and finalizer policy\nretain-until-confirmed-delete;
:Requeue on provisioning, updating, terminating;
}
endif
stop
note right
shared diagram:
shared/diagrams/shared-reconcile-activity.svg
Start from the shared reconcile activity and
specialize provider-backed CRUD, wait, and
status-projection details here.
Controller-local activity diagrams add
list-lookup hints, secret policies, delete
handling, and open formal gaps.
archetype batch: Generated service-manager
controllers specialize the shared reconcile path
with formal runtime ownership.
service: adm
slug: knowledgebase
kind: KnowledgeBase
archetype: generated-service-manager
status/finalizer: required /
retain-until-confirmed-delete
requeue: provisioning, updating, terminating
provider states: create CREATING; update
UPDATING; delete DELETING
follow-up: create=GetWorkRequest ->
GetKnowledgeBase; update=GetWorkRequest ->
GetKnowledgeBase; delete=GetWorkRequest ->
GetKnowledgeBase/ListKnowledgeBases
confirm-delete
supported drift: definedTags, displayName,
freeformTags
reject before mutate: force-new fields
compartmentId
create-only fields: none
list lookup: oci_adm_knowledge_bases filters
compartmentId, displayName, id; exact
compartmentId plus displayName unique match in
ACTIVE, CREATING, or UPDATING; duplicate matches
fail
conflicts: none
open gaps: none
Reviewed lifecycle mapping treats CREATING as
provisioning, UPDATING as updating, ACTIVE as
success, and DELETING as terminating; FAILED is
terminal and DELETED is only a
delete-confirmation target.
Create, update, and delete responses expose
work-request headers but do not return a
KnowledgeBase body. The runtime resumes through
GetWorkRequest, recovers the affected
KnowledgeBase OCID from work-request resources,
and then rereads GetKnowledgeBase before
settling.
Pre-create reuse only runs when spec.displayName
is present and keeps exact compartmentId plus
displayName matching bounded to ACTIVE,
CREATING, or UPDATING summaries.
Only displayName, freeformTags, and definedTags
reconcile in place; compartmentId remains
replacement-only and
ChangeKnowledgeBaseCompartment stays out of
scope for the published runtime.
Delete keeps the finalizer until the work
request is terminal and GetKnowledgeBase or
fallback ListKnowledgeBases confirms the
resource is gone.
end note
@enduml
